H3.text: What parliamentary seat was not contested on 6 May in the UK general election due to the pre-election death of a candidate. John Boakes

A4.text: The death of UKIP candidate John Boakes from a suspected heart attack, announced on 22 April 2010, caused the poll in the constituency to be postponed until 27 May 2010.

A5.text: Thirsk and Malton was originally scheduled to be contested for the first time at the general election on 6 May 2010.
